markets.title: Will $BTC reach $17000 by January 4?
markets.description:
This market will resolve to “Yes” if any Binance 1 minute BTC/USDT candle titled with a date between 2022/12/28 0:01 through 2023/01/04 23:59 (inclusive) in the ET timezone has a final “High” price of 17000.00 or higher. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No". 

The final relevant candle for this market will be the 1 minute BTC/USDT candle titled "2023/01/04 23:59" in the ET timezone. The resolution source for this market is https://www.binance.com, specifically the BTC/USDT “High” prices currently available at https://www.binance.com/en/trade/BTC_USDT?_from=markets&theme=dark&type=spot with “1m” and “Original” selected on the top bar. 

To see the “High” prices, mouse over particular candles and look at the value after “High: ” at the top of the chart. 

The API url https://api.binance.com/api/v3/klines?symbol=BTCUSDT&interval=1m with relevant startDate and endDate parameters may be used in the event that the chart is unavailable. Please note that this market is about the price according to Binance BTC/USDT, not the price according to other sources or spot markets.

markets.title: Will $ETH hit $1,000 or $2,000 first?
markets.description:
This market will immediately resolve to “1k” if any Coinbase 1 minute candle for ETH-USD between 23 Feb '23 12:00 and 31 Dec '23 23:59 (inclusive) in the ET timezone has a final “Low” price of 1,000.00 or lower before $ETH hits $2,000.

This market will immediately resolve to “2k” if any Coinbase 1 minute candle for ETH-USD between 23 Feb '23 12:00 and 31 Dec '23 23:59 (inclusive) in the ET timezone has a final “High” price of 2,000.00 or higher before $ETH hits $1,000.

If no Coinbase 1 minute candle for ETH-USD between 23 Feb '23 12:00 and 31 Dec '23 23:59 (inclusive) in the ET timezone has a final "Low" price of 1,000.00 or lower, or "High" price of 2,000.00 or higher, this market will resolve 50-50.

The resolution source for this market is https://www.coinbase.com/, specifically the ETH-USD “Low" and "High" prices currently available at https://www.coinbase.com/advanced-trade/ETH-USD with “1m” and “Candles” selected on the top bar.

To see the “Low” and "High" prices, mouse over particular candles and look at the respective values after “L” and "H" at the top of the chart.

Please note that this market is about the price according to Coinbase ETH-USD, not according to other sources or spot markets.

markets.title: WILL $BUSD depeg by April 1?
markets.description:
This market will resolve to “Yes” immediately if all Coinbase 1 minute candles for BUSD-USD for any 24 hour period are below 98 cents, for candles between 09 Mar '23 12:00 and 01 Apr '23 23:59 in the ET timezone. Otherwise, this market will resolve to “No”.

Below 98 cents means the candles have a final “High” price below 0.98000 (i.e. 0.97999 or lower). A 24h period of BUSD below 98 cents that starts on the last day will count (e.g. 01 Apr '23 22:00 to 02 Apr '23 22:00).

The resolution source for this market is https://www.coinbase.com/, specifically the BUSD-USD “High” prices currently available at https://www.coinbase.com/advanced-trade/BUSD-USD with “1m” and “Candles” selected on the top bar. To see the “High” prices, mouse over particular candles and look at the value after “H” at the top of the chart.

Please note that this market is about the price according to Coinbase BUSD-USD. If Coinbase stops having the necessary BUSD information to resolve this market, a consensus of credible sources for whether BUSD was below 98 cents for 24h+ may be used to resolve this market.

markets.title: Will 'Shazam! Fury of the Gods' gross more than $30 million domestically on its opening weekend?
markets.description:
'Shazam! Fury of the Gods' (2023) is an upcoming American Superhero film directed by David F. Sandberg. It is the sequel to Shazam! (2019) and the 12th installment in the DC Extended Universe (DCEU). It is scheduled for theatrical release in the USA on March 17, 2023.

This is a market on how much ‘Shazam! Fury of the Gods' will gross domestically on its opening weekend. The “Domestic Weekend” tab on https://www.boxofficemojo.com/title/tt10151854/ will be used to resolve this market once the values for the opening weekend (Mar 17 - 19) are final (i.e. not studio estimates).

This market will resolve to "Yes" if ‘Shazam! Fury of the Gods’ grosses more than $30,000,000 on its opening weekend. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

Opening weekend is defined as the first Friday, Saturday, and Sunday of the film's release. Please note, this market will resolve according to the Box Office Mojo number under Domestic Weekend for the 3-day weekend, regardless of whether domestic refers to only the USA, or to USA and Canada, etc.

If there is no final data available by April 3, 2023, 11:59:59 PM ET, another credible resolution source will be chosen.

markets.title: Will the FDV of OpenSea's token be above $5b 1 week after launch?
markets.description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if the Fully Diluted Valuation of OpenSea's token is above $5,000,000,000 1 week after launch. Otherwise, the market will resolve to "No."

"1 week after launch" is defined as 12:00 PM ET, 7 calendar days after it launches. For example, if the token launches at 8 PM ET, March 15, then the FDV at 12:00 PM ET, March 22 will be used.

The resolution source for this market is CoinGecko, specifically the "Fully Diluted Valuation" metric. The FDV 1 week after launch will be memorialized on the Polymarket market description here: https://polymarket.com/market/will-the-fdv-of-openseas-token-be-above-5b-1-week-after-launch.

If OpenSea doesn't launch a token by December 31, 2023, 11:59:59 PM ET, this market will resolve to 50-50.

markets.title: Arbitrum token FDV >$5b one week after launch?
markets.description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if the Fully Diluted Valuation of Arbitrum's token is above $5,000,000,000 1 week after launch. Otherwise, the market will resolve to "No."

"1 week after launch" is defined as exactly 7 days (168 hours) after the token is claimable. The Arbitrum Foundation has currently announced the token will be claimable on block https://etherscan.io/block/countdown/16890400.

Fully Diluted Valuation (FDV) = Current Price x Max Supply

The resolution source for this market is a consensus of highly liquid sources of $ARB's FDV 1 week after launch. If Arbitrum doesn't launch a token by December 31, 2023, 11:59:59 PM ET, this market will resolve to 50-50.

markets.title: Balaji Bet: BTC > $1m USD on June 17?
markets.description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if 1 BTC is worth more than $1,000,000.00 USD at any time on June 17, 2023 (ET timezone). Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

The resolution source for this market will be consensus of highly liquid price sources for BTC. 

This market will not resolve until June 17 has passed.

markets.title: Will 'Avatar: The Way of Water' gross more than $650 million domestically by January 31, 2023?
markets.description:
'Avatar: The Way of Water' (2022) is an upcoming American action adventure fantasy sci-fi film produced by 20th Century Studios. It is the second installment of the Avatar film series directed by James Cameron. It is scheduled for theatrical release in the USA on December 16, 2022.

This is a market on how much 'Avatar: The Way of Water' will gross domestically by January 31, 2023 (inclusive). The “Domestic Daily” tab on https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl3372254721/ will be used to resolve this market, specifically the "To Date" column.

This market will resolve to "Yes" if 'Avatar: The Way of Water' grosses more than $650,000,000 domestically by January 31, 2023. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

If any finalized numbers in the "To Date" column (for dates January 31, 2023 and before) show a value of more than $650 million, this market will resolve immediately to "Yes." 

This market may only resolve to "No" once the January 31, 2023 "To Date" number is finalized, or if Jan 31, 2023 date is not available, the nearest previous date with available data.
